They'd cook - cook in the living room. Yes, had - had no fireplace in the kitchen. No, just a - that's the only fireplace there was in the house. And a - a small - small cottage - cottage range - cottage range you know. Just a lit
tle fireplace and an oven. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 So the kitchen was .....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 The kitchen was just a - well, more like a shed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What time did you have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}
{\xmlattrvalue 19}}}Half past seven{\*\xmlclose}. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Would you all eat breakfast together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Your father didn't have to eat earlier or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Well of course if - if - dad - if father was days he'd go on duty at seven. But he had his breakfast down there and we used to take his dinner down when we come from school. Come - come from school - 
might be me, might be my brother, might be girl - take it down in the can - hot you see and we used to take our own with us so we had our dinner with him and then come back to school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you enjoy that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Sometimes they used to fall down with it and spill the lot. That - that didn't matter much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 I don't expect he was too pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 I don't know so much about being pleased. That all depends what mood dad was in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 And Jonathon wasn't living there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, no, Jonathon used to come just for the - holiday time from school you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What did you usually have for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Well all depends what mother - mother'd got. Might be soup - in the wintertime it'd be soup. Yes. Pigs - bulls head or pigs head or something like that. Lentils, peas, all things like that. My mother was a good cook. We wasn't starved at any time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you have tea at breakfast time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Yes. Yes, had tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What would your father have for breakfast, you said he had it at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh hes 
did - well he'd take what mother packed up. He'd got a stove down there with an oven and everything you see. Used to keep his own teapot and everything down there. Tea. Take it down from home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you have anything different for breakfast on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Well - we - we always had something - we always had something for - for breakfast. Might be - might be sausages, might be - pork. Things like - and dad used to keep his own pigs you see. Yes. Dad used to keep his own pigs well - there was always cert
ain amount }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7173125\charrsid16386455 that - left home, he used to se}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
ll the other - best port of it - the legs and things like that. Mother'd make soup with the - head or spare parts and - that used to last a week perhaps with - make it in a big boiler.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Yes. Make dumplings - put it in - you know what dumplings are do you. Little puddings - suet puddings, not in a cloth or anything, just - put 'em in the soup, the soup boiler.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What time would you have your {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}}midday{\*\xmlclose} meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well that all depends what time we come out of school. That'd be about - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}}twelve thirty{\*\xmlclose}
. At that time we used to come out of school - we used to come out of school at twelve well we used to go down to the station one of us - with dad's dinner and - and - the one that take it down, 
there's two dinners in the one can you see, dad used to share it out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 That was your main dinner of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 That was the main dinner, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What sort of things would you have for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well anything that mother - mother could make. Like - was always meat of some sort and pudding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Yes, every day. Pudding and things like that. Soup. It might be soup perhaps we'd had for breakfast and - and dinner as well. That all depends - if dad killed a pig of course there wa
s always a lot of - well we used to call it ofal. What you couldn't put in a shop or anything like that, see. If he killed a pig it was - all be sold in the village. Leg here and a leg there and he used to kill one for himself like - so we always had plen
ty of bacon hanging up on the ceiling you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did your mother cure it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Yes, dad cured it. That used to be our job, every time we went into the kitchen we used to have to put some pickling on it - there always used to be a cup or something in the - in a big tub you see, under the table and we used -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How long would that go on for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Well long as we kept - kept it covered for a little while - five minutes perhaps. Whenever we did go in there - anyone went into the kitchen at all it was only to do something to it - all of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was there a butchers in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Yes, a butcher in the village, yes, a butcher in the village and the butcher used to buy the pig. He'd come and kill the pig perhaps and then - always managed - dad - dad
 would sell it and keep what he wanted you see. He might kill a pig and not have any of it at all, he might kill the pig and take it down to Harwich - engine drivers and things like that. A leg here and a head there, somewhere. And the only thing then tha
t we had from the pig was the - ofal - you know, the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Would your mother ever get meat from the butchers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, every - every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 That was for Sunday was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 That - get it Saturday for Sunday - Sunday joint.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was there a special arrangement with the butcher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 And - and midweek as well if we wanted anything for soup or anything like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What would you have for your evening meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Only had the one room to do the lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What would you eat for your evening meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What - ordinary - ordinary meals you mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 In the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Evening? May be a bun as a rule, we - well we used to go - we never used to have anything after - after we had tea. We used to have tea about {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 17}}}five o'clock{\*\xmlclose} and after tea we used to go to bed but - might have our - and go to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What did you have for your tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What the - bread and cheese. Again might soup - all depends what - all depends what mother's got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you have tea to drink then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, we - mother us
ed to make lemonade - oatmeal - drink. Different - different kinds of drink mother used to make. Used to go and help ourselves when we wanted.
