\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Not when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, no. No. That used to be - of course they used to be stuff to the workers you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did she make wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Parsnip wine.
 Oh what's the name of it - sloe - sloe wine - sloe wine, sloe wine, sloe gin. All of us never drank it, nor did dad. Dad was teetotal and mother was a teatotaller. And - and - when - when I moved into that house and when dad died I threw - I threw away a
bout a do}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7173125\charrsid16386455 z}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
en bottles of different wine that was made - years and years old. Man'd stood on his head if he'd have drank it. They didn't half - the builder didn't half make a song about it too - because I threw it away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Who'd have drunk it at the time}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7173125\charrsid16386455  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 - who did she make it for?
