\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Do you ever remember seeing your mother having a bit less so she could keep your plates full?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Oh yes, oh yes, yes, yes, yes, yes, we used to have second helpings sometimes like that. And sometimes we'd have the - all depends what there was - sometimes have the - what was
 cut cold in the safe for - for breakfast next morning. But the wintertime we always had - we always had soup for breakfast. Either pea soup or - some different soup.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Talk? Well - that all depends what conv
ersation we was in. We couldn't - we couldn't do much talking. I tell you dad used to have a little stick up there - if anything happened - tap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Were you allowed to ask people to pass things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes, we used to - yes used to pass - ask them to pass things like that.
