\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No. Sometimes we used to have a row sometimes -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 That was taken for granted was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 That's right, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did your parents say you should hit back if another child hit you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well they would do if mother was - see us in the back. She'd correct us anyhow. She'd correct the one that was to blame.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 But if you got into a squabble with another child - would she say stand up for yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Yes. Well she'd send us in the kitchen sometimes - the one that she thought was guilty. Stand there for a little while.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 But she wouldn't use the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you'd grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well I suppose they hoped that - carry on as we - as we were were taught but some of us didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Some of you were black sheep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Well I don't know a - black sheep - I don't think there's any of us bad at all. I might have been the worst I don't know but - I never got into trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did they try to make you consider certain things important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What would they be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Used to - converse and one thing and another on different things of course. Try and remain - repent if we were to blame or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 They would talk religiously to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What did they think about swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well - never thought about. No, never thought about that. No more - no more would I now. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 If grown ups were talking could you join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What - when
 we were children? Well that all depends that doesn't it. If that was - private - private talks, no. But if it was anything for our good, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How old were you when you began to be able to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was there a change when you left school for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
No, no, I - I left school when I was - thirteen I was when I left school and then 'course I went to work and about twelve months I done before I left home. Then I left home and - I sailed at Mistley, I left right away, then I went f
rom there to Kenneth, Kenneth to Framlingham, Framlingham to Melton. Now that was the four years practically I was on me own - I was three years on me own, when I was at Mistley of course I was at home. Used to go to Sunday school and on the choir and eve
rything the same - the as I did when I was at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 But at the other places you went and lived in the other towns?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 When your father used the cane you said you felt that was quite fair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes. He just - do it across the table like - that's about the only time ever he used the cane when we was at the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 There wasn't a time when you felt it was mean or unjust?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, no, I don't think so. Everything - we deserved it at that time although we didn't think so perhaps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Can you remember a time when it happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 I remember one time having a good thrashing 'cos I said something to mother that I shouldn't have done and she told him.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 I don't know what it was now. Mother had to come into 
the kitchen to stop him giving me the stick anyhow. She said, you - you - that's enough, stop it. He used to loss his temper you see. But - otherwise - mother used to have us punished, at the same time she wouldn't have done excess. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 She didn't want it to go too far?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
No. I said something to mother one day that I shouldn't have done, that's the only - that's the only thrashing that I ever did have. And - I say, me mother had to come and stop - 'cos he didn't do it outside, he used to take us in
 the kitchen you see. Had a stick there. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Do you think you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents or do you think one played a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7173125\charrsid16386455 No, no, both - both}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455  the same - both the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Oh yes, we always had a birthday - always had birthday cake and - home made cake of course. The same by - Christmas times. Especially if dad was at home, used to have - apples str
ung up on the ceiling and you know - hands tied behind your back. And perhaps that was smothered in flour or something like that. Used to have some games like that. The same by Christmas trees - parcels on Christmas trees - used to have our names on or nu
mbers, I don't recollect, perhaps there'd be a piece of coal - well that was a piece of fun. Yes. That was all part.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was this just the family or did you have friends in at Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well might have one or two next door neighbours perhaps. At Chr
istmas time. but - I think it was different there - I mean eggs was thirty six a shilling. Eggs thirty-six a shilling you know. Milk - three pints a penny. We used to go to the farm and get it - skimmed milk, they used to take the - cram off it you know T
hree pints a penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Makes a difference doesn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
It do. And thirty - thirty-six eggs a shilling. Thirty-six oranges - sometimes forty. Yes. The same size oranges as what you have to pay for or fivepence now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you have friends in on your birthdays for parties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well they'd only be the next door - next door people and youngsters. We never had a - like they do now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 There was quite a big family next door did you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. About - about - I think it was seven or eight. About t
he - well nearly the same as - nearly the same as ours. 'Cos they used to go away from home when they got about thirteen the youngsters - twelve or thirteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you have any musical instruments in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 May used to play the concertina and 
we used to have a - in fact I think we had two. Two musical boxes. And mother used to be able to play a dulcimer do you call it - with a stick, used to play that. Mother - mother could play she concertina lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Would you sing when she did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes sometimes - of course dad - dad couldn't. We used to sing Sunday afternoons sometimes. Hymns and one thing and another.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What else would you sing besides hymns?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Never had anything else. Might - might sing songs what we heard at school you know.
 I couldn't tell you what they were now. And we used to play and sing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did any of the children play anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 I believe that's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7173125\charrsid16386455  the - that's the laundry I bel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7173125\charrsid16386455 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 ve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was there anyone else in the family who played anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Me brother wha
t's alive he - he could play a cornet. And - 'cos he's been in the Navy you see. He - he - bugler of course he could play a cornet you see. And the oldest brother - I told - he didn't play - he didn't blow an instrument but he was a snare drummer. Yes. In
 the Salvation Army, when the Salvation Army gave up he - they j}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7173125\charrsid16386455 oined a - a - mission band in I}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7173125\charrsid16386455 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 wich.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 When you were a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 When he was a youngster. I - I think I showed - I showed you the photo with - him in uniform.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did your parents play games with you when you were children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What would they play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Myself and - dad'd play draughts. We used to go down the signal box sometimes and play with him, sometimes dominoes but - as regards games well we used to play what you'd call school games I expect. And }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5451075\charrsid16386455 - ring-a-ring-aros}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 s and things like that. Round the table. things like that
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Inside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Especially if it was wet - so you couldn't get outside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What else did they do like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Round the maypole bush or whatever they call it I don't know, I forget what they call 'em now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did your father play football with you outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, no. No - no football about then. We only played games that I remember when I went to school was - watching men - quoi
ts. Never - football or anything at that time. Had quoits.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You had your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, no, they were metal quoits. We weren't playing - used to go and watch the the men playing - they were in the league you see, quoit}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5451075\charrsid16386455 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455  league. But there ain't been quoits now for years and years. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You had a Bible in the house and you said you had religious books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Can you remember any titles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 There'd be the Bible there of course. But I'll tell you - the family Bible - my nephew - what die
d I told you suddenly - you see - he - he had the Bible and he - he turned that over to the - they formed a - a M}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5451075\charrsid16386455 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
sonic Lodge - a London Masonic Lodge and he gave the Bible to them. He had it - you know, cleaned and one thing and another and - and turned it over to them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you take a newspaper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. I take the East Anglian and the Daily Mail - every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did your parents take the papers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, I forget the - I'm trying to think of the name - it's a Liberal paper anyway. A Liberal pap
er. Dad was a Liberal. I forget the name of it now, that was done away with and - and - taken over by another paper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was it a national Liberal paper or a Local one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 National - printed in London. I take the East Anglian, that's the Ipswich paper of course and - I take the Daily Mail.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was he a keen Liberal - did he take an active part?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 He was a keen Liberal 'til - 'til they didn't put a L}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5451075\charrsid16386455 ib}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 eral up. Then of course he went Conservative. He didn't vote Labour. I must say I'm the same too. I don't go Labour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Do you remember him doing any work for the Liberal party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes, he used to do canvassing. Yes. Used to do canvassing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 He was a member of the party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did he do anything apart from at election times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, no, no. Unless there was anything - concerning the - the Liberal party. He might fly the colors or some yellow flag or something.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You remember him talking about it do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, oh yes. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Do you remember if you knew why he was a Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Well I expect - his views - I couldn't - I couldn't say that. Of course father's and son they - son goes the father's way sometimes which - I - I voted Liberal 'til - 'til there was no Li}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5451075\charrsid16386455 b}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 eral put up. 'Cos Liberals Conservative now
 you see. Ridsdale. I vote for him of course. And we vote Conservative - I've been voting Conservative since I come out the Navy. 'Cos the simple reason 'cos there was no Liberal put up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did your mother have Liberal views as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Mother - mother was Liberal, yes, yes. Yes. And so was me brothers. At }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8606324\charrsid16386455 
Ipswich}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 . I've one in Birmingham I - I think he's changed his tune now. He - he was Labour but I - I think he's climbed down now. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Do you remember your mother going to vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 They used t
o vote, yes, yes. I go up and vote. You see, if they come down and fetch me. I don't otherwise. But they look out for that, they - they - they don't go for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was there any connection between the railway and being a Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No. No, no, no. Oh no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Your father didn't feel he had to vote for the Liberal party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, no, no, no, no, no. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, they vote according to their own conscience. Of course when father - when dad - was a younger man anyhow was - there was no such a thing as L
iberal - Labour. It was either Conservative or Liberal. Might have been Independent but -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Some people in those days had to vote a certain way to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5451075\charrsid16386455  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 suit their employer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 That's right, yes, that's right, yes, yes. Ame as the farm labourers. They used to have to vote according to what their master was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What were they round here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Liberal as a rule. Majority of 'em were yellow as they called 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did your parents take any magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, they couldn't afford it. No, they took a - th
ey used to take a - well I don't know what you'd call it - a chapel book - yes, a chapel magazine or whatever - something like that. I couldn't tell you the name of that either now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did they ever read aloud to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Read? -Well we used to have to Sunday afternoons I tell you - all the lot of us used to take it in turns, mother, father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 But not apart from that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You say your father used to be a bearer for funerals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Do you remember anyone in the family dying - a funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 I couldn't tell you. I know they used to carry 'em miles - on the shoulder.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did people wear mourning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Yes. Yes, yes, yes. About twelve months I think it was, that all - even for kiddies or babies they'd go 
in the mourning - 'cos the house was in mourning. Some families would - some families would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 When your brothers and sisters died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Would your parents have been in mourning for a long time after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No. Not - not for youngsters they were not -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Not babies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Were you taken out visiting neighbours by your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
We used to - neighbours? Visiting? Oh yes, we used to go visiting. To different - different people and - another thing is the chapel people th
ey - they used to visit one another different house one week you know and have prayer meetings and things like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Extra to the Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, yes. Other than the chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was that on Sundays?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, Sundays you see, yes, Sunday evening. Or they'd go and visit the sick perhaps some - band of them would go and pay a visit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you have relations living near who you'd go and visit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No. Well the near - the nearest relation was Ipswich and we've got several there now as I tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you go and see them when you were children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Oh yes. Well - of course the older brother lived with an aunt well of course we used to go and visit them. Yes, then of course when the oldest one got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8134313 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455  well of course we used to - 
go them. And this - this is one of - one of the oldest brothers sons. He was the only son. Now he's got two sons you see and one of them's got three so there's the Bridges's about and that's the only one that's Bridges in the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 They're all Bridges's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, yes, yes. I'm not }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8134313 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455  and me brother hasn't got a boy you see. Yes. There's some Bridges's to carry on as - there's four at Ipswich you see, one or two of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did your mother take you shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well that all depends if we 
want anything. I - I - I used to go down to Harwich every - every Saturday morning when I was about seven years old - that - to - to I shopping, yes. Grocery and things like that. If she wanted anything - wearing apparel or anything like that well she use
d
 to go to Ipswich or go to a sale or something. Well she - she never had a chance to take many of us I - if she were going shopping. I tell you she used to pay into a clothing club and a boot club. Well that would only be at Manningtree you see. And if sh
e went to Ipswich or anything she - she'd go on a cheap ticket you see - railway worker}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8606324\charrsid16386455 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 s wife.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 That wasn't free - it was just a reduced rate was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 A reduced fee. A quarter fare return. She'd go to Ipswich for about sixpence ha'penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You said you went to London for your holidays one year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 And you stayed there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 I stayed there - 'cos only the three days dad had you see. Three days holiday well it was - with his brother - brother and his wife.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You stayed with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 We stayed with them, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What sort of things did you do on that holiday in London?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Well - I went - went to - visit - go in the shops and one thing and another. And they worked in shops you see they - that was - oh, Whiteleys. Whiteleys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was that the uncle that worked at Whiteleys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. That was a big one and the other one was - Selfridges. Those shops are bigger now than they were when we went to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did they seem like big stores to you then though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 They were, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you go sightseeing when you were in London?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well we went to - I don't know whether it was as youngster or whether I was out - White-City and Olympia.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How did the big City seem to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Madame Tussaud}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8606324\charrsid16386455 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 s and - and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 That was when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 That was when - that was wonderful to go up to London when we were kiddies. Of course dad only had the four days holiday you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you do anything on Bank holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Go down to seaside somewhere. Go - pony cart or w
agonette there used to be then you know - four - four wheeler with side seats. And you used to go to Clacton in one of them. Horse and cart - horse and cab you see. So of course - of course time before we used to go by train - cheap ticket.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Where did you get the horse and trap from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
In the village a man had a horse and trap - hired it, yes. Dad used to drive it. Sometimes - the man'd come too. That all depends how many we got to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you think that was fun?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes, rather.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 When you went to London did you all go - the whole family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, no, no, only one or two, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was that a high time of the year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Perhaps - perhaps there'd only be - if mother went up she'd take one girl, if my dad went up he'd take a boy 
or so. That's how - never all went together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Someone went every year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You say your mother would take the girls up to London sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, well she'd go by herself then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How often would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well all depends - what - what the - what the shop wanted you see. They'd send an order in and - dad'd get them as soon as ever he could.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 That was once a month?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, yes, that might be twice - twice in a month. If they wanted the birds.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What else happened o
n Saturdays - you said you went shopping then you'd these choers for your parents, what else did you do in your free time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well - I don't know, we used to - clean or something - chop wood for the week or some - one cleaned the boots and - the girls'd
 do something else - clean spoons or something or other. We all had a job - what could do anything
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What about Sundays - you didn't do anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No. Oh no, no, not at Sundays.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you have different clothes to wear on Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Oh
 yes. Yes, if we had'em. Very strict on that - no boots and everything. Never wore Sunday boots only Sundays or when we went out you know, when we was in our best rig.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Could you play games when you were wearing your best rig?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Not Sundays no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Your parents thought it was wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Didn't you go off sometimes on Sunday where they couldn't see you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 I went down - down and jumped over a ditch with - the Sunday suit on and went in. Yes, I got a hiding for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was there a chapel in the village where your parents could go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 A chapel? Two chapels in Bradfield.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was there always?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. One chapel has closed now. They amalgamated and they closed the one chapel and made it into a - a hall. The - they can let
 but - they're not allowed liquor or anything. No weddings or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did both your parents go to chapel on Sunday morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 When they could get there, yes. I tell you that - dad was the - duty one week you see. If he didn't go in the
 morning he'd go at evening. But mother never went at evening time 'cos - putting the youngsters to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did they take all the children when they went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, they all went to church Sunday school. To the church Sunday school - not the chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You didn't go to the chapel service either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
No. We - no, no, cos I tell you me and me brother was in the choir - church choir 'til I left school - 'til I left school. Mother couldn't get us ready in time to go to chapel so the youngest one was the o
nly one that went. Well of course she was eight years younger than any of us you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, we went to Sunday school outings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How often would they take place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well now, only ever once in a - once in a twelve months you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 In the summer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, in the summer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Where did they go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well - I've been to Clacton, Lowestoft, Yarmouth. White City. Crystal Palace.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What did they do when they got there - play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, they'd take you to so}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8606324\charrsid16386455 me interesting place - Madame T}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 ussaud}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8606324\charrsid16386455 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
s or something like that you see. Used to have a meal - a meal at some place. That was all booked you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 When you were in the choir were you paid for it or was it all voluntary?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well we used to get - we used
 to get about half a crown at Christmas and the outing you see. Was a dinner and tea and the - the outing you see. We was out for the day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you do anything else with the Sunday school - were there any clubs in connection with it, like temperance clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, no, no, no. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No. Used to have the - a Saturday I think it was, they had the the boot club and clothes club. One of us used to go up and pay that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Not social club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Who taught you to say them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Dad. Dad. We all used to do that. Before we went to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 And you had the readings on Sunday afternoons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you have family prayers otherwise?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Not ; not Sundays, no, no. We used to go to chapel. I tell you we used to go to church three times - three times a Sunday as a rule.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What did your parents do when they weren't working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 I don't know when they weren't - they were always working if that's - that's only the truth anyway. 'Cos there was nothing done Sundays.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Your father had his gardening didn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Yes, garden at home, garden down at - on the railway line - on the railway line.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 He had an allotment there didn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 He had allotment down there - he used to pay so much a year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 He didn't have any hobbies that he like to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Only - bird catching as I tell you and clock mending and - repairing boots and one thing and another. Yes, because we never had anything to do, we never did anything like that after we left home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did your mother have any interests outside the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, only the tailoring as I tell you. There's nothing on Sunday of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 There wasn't any village group that she belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, no, there was nothing like - there was no such a thing as groups at that time. No mothers union or - or the Women}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8606324\charrsid16386455 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 s Institute or anything like that you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 There was no where for her to go out of the house to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, no, no, no. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 She was no gossiper woman. Chance time is it'd be a neighbour perhaps. Come in or - or she might go and visit somebody that's ill or anything. But she never had much time to go gadding about as they call it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did your father take part in any sport at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well - Sunday - school
 sports you know - take on - races or things like that. When - when he was off duty you see. If he - if he was on night duty he used to have to go to bed of a afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 But he enjoyed sports did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, oh yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 He was a good sportsman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Yes, we - with kiddies of course. You know the races different ages. Of course there was no football or cricket or anything like that at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What else besides racing - jumping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Do that - at the Sunday school sports of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You said you didn't have anyone to help your mother in the house apart from the lady who did the washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 That's all - that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 If she was ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh I was going to say, confinement or anything like that of course she did have.
 Used to have a - one of them nurses at that time they used to be - midwives didn't they. Midwives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was that someone in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Somebody in the village - two or three in the village there were that used to come.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did a friend come in to help her with the housework?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
No, we used to do it and dad used to do it, yes, no - nobody come in we had nowhere to sleep 'em you see. They - they used to come in of a morning you see and get us ready for school and - and then go away again and then come back and prepare the meals.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 That would be the midwife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, the midwife you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 So she was a sort of maid as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, that's right. Yes. She'd come back during the day I expect - similar to that. There was no - government aid at that time..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 The nearest relatives you had were in Ipswich weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, in - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 And you used to go over and see your brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, I go there now. They come over and fetch me you see. In fact they were here Sunday - br
ought me some cakes and apple tarts and jam tarts. And my great-great-nephews.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 While you were living at home how often would you go over to Ipswich or how often would they come over here to see each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well - one of the family, mother or one of the girls used to go over to Ipswich every week for shopping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 And they'd pop in then would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes, they'd come in for the day you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 And the Ipswich relations would come over here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh they would come over - yes, yes. They
 used to come by cheap train of a Sunday - to Mistley station and then walk and we used to go and meet them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 When your brother got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8134313 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455  he lived in Ipswich - the one who lived with the aunt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 He set up house there did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 He - he lived - he lived in Ipswich and - well all his family live in Ipswich you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did they come back here on Sunday and that kind of thing to see you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes, they used to come - say they used to come to Mistly station by train - used to cost about sixpence I think Sunday, at that time.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did your parents have friends in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Only - casual friends. No - no relations or any - mother never made a lot of - well she was friendly with everybody but she didn't make frien
ds to - to - always be gossiping about - she had too much - she had too much time to - making clothes one thing and another as I said. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 I wonder if she missed much life in the village because she wouldn't gossip?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No. No, no, of course - there
 was no life in the village at that time 'cos there; was no institute or mothers union or anything like that at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did the housewives tend to meet somewhere for a good old }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433687\charrsid16386455 m}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 atter together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh I don't think so. No I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Your mother behaved quite normally did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
I know the - Mrs Hamlyn was one of the housewives, Mrs Cowell was another one that used to come - and look after mother when - had the youngsters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 But they weren't special friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, just - paid servants.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Would your mother go and help them in return?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
No, nothing of that - she never had time with all the family she had. No. She'd do a bit - anybody a hand's turn of course. She used to do their shopping for them or anything like that if 
- if she was going to Ipswich and they wanted anything she'd get it for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 She'd fit it in with her normal work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did your father have friends of his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Only - you mean personal friends? Yes, yes, chapel people and that's al
l. 'Cos he - he lived at Holland well that's only about ten miles away you see - he was born there and his - half brothers and sisters were there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did he see a lot of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Not all - very often. Day - day when he's day off or anything like he'd 
bike over. He was the first man to have a bike in - a push bike in - in Bradfield. Yes. There was solid}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455  t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10433687\charrsid16386455 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 res}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
 round about the size of your finger you know the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455  t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10433687\charrsid16386455 y}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 re}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10433687\charrsid16386455 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 . They used - yes, he used to bike over to see them. Brothers and sisters. His half brothers
 and sisters. The youngest one went out to America - the youngest brother I showed you. In fact I had a letter from him - a fortnight ago from America. There's tow of 'em coming over again - father and son. They were over - well, the father was over three
 years ago and he went back and she died. So he - the son is over here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was this the brother who you told me about the character on parchment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. That's - that's the - that's the son - - that's the son of course. Yes, the father's dead - died before dad did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Could you tell me that story again about the fellow who worked for Whileleys who wanted to to America?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes, he - he - he gave his notice in and - what they asked him, what do you want to leave for? And he told them he - he was 
going out to America to better himself. He said, I don't blame you in the least, he says, in that case, he said, I'll give you a parchment - character on parchment. And he did so. And as soon as he stepped ashore in America he got a job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was there somebody waiting at the dock to employ people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Well I expect they were there or something. He got off the boat and somebody approached him I expect and - he told 'em what he wanted and that's what he got. He done a certain time there and - left. For to 
better himself of course. And the same master come and asked him if he was out of a job. He said, no, he said, I'm not out of a job, he said. He said, will you come back to me. Well, he said, I'll come back, he says, but - I'm an American citizen now.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did he marry an American girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, no, he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8134313 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
 a Yorkshire girl. She - she went out - I think it was Yorkshire - up North anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 He me}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10433687\charrsid16386455 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
 her here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. I expect - in London I expect, yes, yes. 'Cos when they were over here - lets see, 
before dad died - dad's been dead twenty years this year - they come over about two years, him and his wife came over and they went to see her people and they made their home next door you see. For a month, then they - soon as they got back she passed awa
y.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 So you kept in touch with them anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes. Yes, yes. Yes, I get letters from them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did your parents have the same friends - did they share people they knew - your father knew people from chapel you said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. They - otherwise th
ey didn't gossip much. And of course - Bradfield at that time you remember there was one house here and another one half a mile away. All these - all these - all these houses have been built since I've been out the Navy. All the council houses where there
's ten - ten, twenty, thirty, thirty-six, forty-two - fourty-six. There were fifty council houses to my knowledge. They've all been built. Then of course along here - all the private houses have been built in the last three years.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You can't remember how big the village was then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
No, well I can't - I could tell you if I sat long enough to - there was only three houses down this road for a start so far as the station. None down Harwich Road and in the street of course there's a lot of them pulled d
own now as you see when you come through.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Were there other people working on the railways lived in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No. Only two signalmen. Four platelayers as we call them and - porter and a station master who lived at the - at the station house. T
hat's all there was on the railway then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did these people live in the other houses by the railway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, they lived all over the village. Yes. Yes. Lived all over the village.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Were friends of your parents ever invited into the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh
 yes, oh yes, yes. Socially of course. There used to be sometimes - 'cos I tell you dad used to be on night duty every other week, well Sunday night when he was off there used to be some of them come down to the house and - have a - prayer meeting or some
thing of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 So when they did come in it would be a sort of religious meeting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
When they did come in - yes. Yes. Of course we used to be in bed, lot of us they used to come down. And dad used to go up to the chapel to the prayer meetings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 But they wouldn't be asked in for a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, no, no, no, no. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Or a cup of tea or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Well - I don't know whether mother used to make them a cup of tea I'm sure. They were very sociable anyway - with the people. They were all cha
pel people of course. Still - dad - anything at the church - anything about - if he was wanted he'd - he'd go. And if we had a party - you know, at the - same as the - Boer War - when they finished, you know, Boer War well you know they had a big dinner p
arty or something, he used to go and carve and one thing and another,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Where was that held?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
At the - where the - that was the Rectory at that time but of course it's - a - old people's home now. The Rectory's down here, the new one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Who was asked to that dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh all the village.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Everyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Youngster as well. Oh yes. We had a subscription I expect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Can you remember what happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, I was in the Navy at that time you see. I wrote dad - I heard dad talk about 
it and - brothers and sisters, younger ones, talk about it. What fun they had, one thing and another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Would there have been dancing and that kind of thing?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well - races and things like that see. Few fi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9047188\charrsid16386455 reworks I expect - tu}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 penny squibs or something of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Can you remember an occasion like that that you were present at?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
No. No. We - we used to have the annual school treats of course. Racing and one thing and another. Bag of sweets or something of that - winner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 That's just the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Just the children - different ages you know. Toddlers and - older ones. And as I tell you, the choirboys used to go for an outing every year. Canon Norvan was the - having the living or whatever you call it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 He was Church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You said your mother made the wine out of the various berries and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did she offer that to the people who called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes, yes, yes - a glass of - especially the men - delivering coal or anything like that they - have
 a glass of her wine - piece of cake. Sloe wine - elderberry wine. Parsnip wine. Mead - from the honeycomb, used to keep - make that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Christmas was quite a family affair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh that was-a family affair yes. Christmas Day especially. The evening time - serving out the - Christmas tree.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You were saying about the presents you had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Piece of coal wrapped up in paper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What sort of things would you give each other as real presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well they used to get - of course mum and dad al
ways used to give a lot of these sugar things you know. Clocks and - clocks and all mice and things like that. They all used to go on the Christmas tree. Oh we always had plenty for Christmas time. I tell you oranges were thirty-six a shilling then - fort
y sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did friends drop in casually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes. Yes, yes. And we used to go - we used to go to other parties and they used to come to ours. Used to return the compliments like.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What sort of thing would happen at the party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Why - all the school youngsters. Ring-a-roses or something like that, kiss in the ring or something of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Were they in the afternoon or evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Afternoon and evening. They'd have tea of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 When you say your father talked a lot of politics would that be with his chapel friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well - the whole village. He - he used to be yellow then - liberal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 That would be anyone he met he would talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes, yes, yes. They used to put the colors on you know when they - the voting day th
ey'd have their colors on. And one old chap, his name was Gilbert, he was a strict Liberal and he used to go round collect about Tories party and dad say to him, I - you know, he says all right Charlie, he says, that's all right, he says, they're voting a
ll right, he says, but - plenty of beer about. He could do it too - he could drink.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 The party workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Yes, and the donkey cart. He used to go round for people - at Jake's Hall, what lived at Jakes Hall at the time well they were all Conservativ
es of course, higher people. Well some of them are anyway. Most of them were at that time. And - of course farmers and that they were all blue.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Farmers were blue were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Yes. And the - their men of course they were - they were yellow well they they - they'd wear the green just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Who else would be blue in the village? Were people who kept the shop for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well they're all - all employers - they're all Conservatives of course. Don't blame 'em either come to that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You've changed yourself haven't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 That's what they want in next Parliament I think, but I don't know whether they'd do much good - now. I don't think - it matters much.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Many people divided society up into sort of groups or social classes, before 1918 were you aware of groups like that in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No. 'Cos I was in the Navy in then. I was in the Navy then up 'til 1922. So what took place in the village then I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 When you were a youngster?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, when I was a youngster of course - I was a youngster then 'cos I went away as a youngster practically.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did your parents feel separate from the village because your father's job was not an agricultural one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh no, no, no, no. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Used to mix up with them of course. Oh 
no, that - he - he was a working man the same as anybody else. Earn about a shilling a day more perhaps - or a shilling a week more than they did. They were only getting nine or ten shillings a week on the land and dad got about ten shillings, he worked t
welve hours a day you see. Thirty-six hours the weekends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 But you didn't feel the farmers were in a different sort of social group to yourselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, they all mixed up together. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Even people working on the land?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How about the parsons who lived in the big house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Some - some of 'em were all right and some - wasn't. They used to visit us and - and there's one I think that - be - in fact mother took Morris, me brother off the choir on account of him. But - the Canon
 Norvan - heard him singing in the - in the - Sunday out - heard him singing in the choir - in the - audience like and they wanted to know who he was. And why isn't he in the choir? Oh he's - we sent him - I don't know, he done something I expect. But - h
e had to come back and apologi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9047188\charrsid16386455 z}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
e to mother. He - he was - he didn't want - he didn't want chapel people in church choirs. But he - he had to come and apologi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9047188\charrsid16386455 z}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
e. Mother said - and he said, he said if you give me an apology, he says. I'll - I'll let him come 
back again. Well he used to sing the solos you see. Yes. Sing the solos and they had - they had him - they - as it happened he used to to Manningtree school where I did and as it happened that week they'd been p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9047188\charrsid16386455 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 acti}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9047188\charrsid16386455 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
ing that hymn - the tune. and nobody in the church knew it and he sung it right through himself you see. Yes. And they - that's when they wanted to know why - why he wasn't on the choir.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 He had to apologi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9047188\charrsid16386455 z}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 e?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, he - they took him back. He come and see mother, mother said well, she
 says if you give me an apology she says, he'll come back, she says if not, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you think it was an unusual thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 He was a - he was a cripple for one thing and he says this is my living Mrs Bridges he says, and - and I shall be losing it. H
e says, I shall be losing it if things happen be reported on that. Well she says that's up to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you think it very unusual for the Canon to come and apolog}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9047188\charrsid16386455 iz}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 e to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. I mean, of course - mother didn't speak about it I don't ex
pect for one minute. But that's what - happened. He was a cripple and - well practically come crying to mother you see. And she told him, she said, if you like to apologi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10894320\charrsid16386455 z}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 e he can come back again. That was after this - this Cannon Norvan - I think it was Cannon Norvan - wanted to know why he wasn't on the choir you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Were you ever told to touch your cap to people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Who would you do that to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh all the - all the people that lived down here - people down at Jekes hall. All t
he - well parsons and everything else. Well we used to have to do that at school when the - clergyman used to come in for the scripture lessons - always we used to have to salute - stand up and salute - good morning sir, one thing and another. -That was a
 usual thing for the boys to salute and the boys to bend their knee you know. Oh yes, yes, curtsey.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did your mother teach your sisters to curtsey?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes, yes, oh used to have to do it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Would you do it to your neighbours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh the -
 yes, oh church people and everything else, yes, yes. Well of course I mean to say - I say, all bar the - we were all church school. Sunday school you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You'd show respect to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was there anyone in the village you wouldn't have touched your cap to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
No, I don't think so. No, no. There's certain people we used - I mean to say we didn't salute the farmers or anything like that. Just the - parson and his wife and people down here, well they were all big church people and pe
ople down at Jakes Hall. Well they were the upkeep of the church practically.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 So people you didn't come into contact with you wouldn't salute?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, no, no, no, no. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 The people at Jakes Hall - was th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10894320\charrsid16386455 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 t the Canon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, no, no, no. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No - might be the church people as a rule but that changed hands several times. While we were there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 But they were considered important people were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes, yes, at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 I don't know I'm sure - just what we was brought up to I expect. At school. Curtsey this and curtsey that a or - bow here and bow there.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did the people at Jakes Hall own a lot of - he land in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well all this farm - all these farms belonged to Jakes Hall at that time but they've been separated - sold you see - separated.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 At that time the farmers weren't land owners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
No, no, they were all - belonged to the - well the Norman estate it was at that time. All these farms round here belonged to - the Canon Norman to - Mist
ley. You know - when you come - which way to you come? Do you come through Langtree town? Do you come along by the water? From Manningtree. Well on the right hand side when you're coming this way there's a park well that's that's - that was the Canon Norm
an's estate. He lived in that house. Well now at the present time that}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10894320\charrsid16386455 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
s Brooks and Sons - canteen and one thing and another - they've turned it into a canteen - club.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was he the one who was the J.P. as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 And he was quite a big figure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh he was a big figure at that time, yes. Yes, he was a big figure at that time but he come a cropper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How's that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well - all these farms - all these farms round here belonged to a certain - person, some relation to Canon Norman a
nd - Canon Norman - I couldn't say - explain it exactly but - he - he sold a lot of the farms to his son. He bought the farms or something of that or turned them over to his sons and - the older son should have belonged - they should have belonged to the 
older son - the Squire. And - the Squire }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8134313 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455  - a daughter }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8134313 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455  a solic}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10894320\charrsid16386455 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
tor and he found there was something gone wrong and he - made enquiries and one thing and another and all these farms shouldn't have been sold at all, 'cos they should have gone t
o the eldest son you see. So - well, Parson Hill was one - he had Bradfield Hall. That'd be on the left}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10894320\charrsid16386455 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
hand side on the Straight Road as you go past the Post Office. That's - that was one farm. Another one was on Mistley Heath. Well they sold another one 
in Grantham and he bought the farms and gave them to his sons. Well they all had to refund it - give 'em back to the estate - give 'em back to the estate. Rudlers - Rudlers Royce was the - saw to that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 So that was a great embarrassment to the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, he - he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8134313 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455  - he }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8134313 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455  one of the daughters you see. So - the old grandfather had been robbing all the - eldest sons you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Were the people shocked by this when the story went round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You say he came a cropper?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, well he - he had go give up and go away of course. Two or three of them went out of the - over the heads about it too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What sort of people in the village went to the church and what sort of people went to the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well the majority
 - majority of the chapel people of course were farm labourers. The other - of course what did go to church there was farmers and their wives and family. And some of the workmen. Of course at that time some of the work - workmen had to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was that because of their job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Because of their job. Same by voting or anything. Still that was a secret vote they - they needn't have been so strict about it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Do you think when people were actually inside the polling booth they did actually vote the way they wanted to vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Yes, of course they didn't know did they. Secret vote you see, they - they - the farmer wouldn't know whether his man voted - for what the man he wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 On the whole would you say that grander people went to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes - the top people, yes, oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 But they'd make some of their workers go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Who would the Canon have mixed with in the village - would he have known anyone socially?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Who? Canon? Well - just ordinary people. One - on
e of his daughters lived - at this house down here. another one was - serving at the Rectory you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 So you would have mixed with the clergyman and his family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No one else though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How about the teachers at the school, who would they have mixed with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Teachers they were all in the church choir. All the lot of them were church choir I think. They used to have a big choir here at one time. Now I think there's about five in the choir now I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Who do you think the teachers would have seen socially in the evenings and outside their work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Oh they used to - have the youngsters there if they were having a concert at all, if there was a concert in the village, they'd have 'em practicing and one
 thing and another. Yes, mix around. The chapel and church as well of course - at the weekday school concert. Used to be held over the Rectory - had a hall over there Parish Hall, but that was sold and pulled down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Who would the farmers mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Farmers? Well - there's two farmers - there's two farmers used to belong to the chapel. But all the others was church as I remember.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Would most of their friends be farmers or would they have friends outside? Would your father and his workmates be friends with farmers?

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes, yes, oh yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was there anyone else in the village who employed people besides the farmers and railways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No. I mean the shops - the shops all the - the shop owners was their own - serving. They never h
ad anybody in the shop you see, only themselves. Same with the Post Office. The Post Office was a shop as well. At that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Were the shopkeepers looked on as slightly different people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, no, no. No. Just ordinary working people that's all. H
aving no bit shopkeepers of course. Only Spicers about the biggest shop we've had here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Do you think most people had the same standard of living in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, I think so, yes. Don't think there was much difference - I mean to say, shopkee
pers were only - some of them - the man was working on a farm or something of that, at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 So they'd be doing two things at once?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 That was just a - side - a side - a sideshow that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Would his wife perhaps run the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 That's right - yes, or daughter or something like - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How much money do you think they'd be living off a week the shopkeepers - they'd be getting a bit more that way wouldn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes. Yes, they'd get a little; bit more. They didn't make so much profit as what they do today I don't expect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 There was no way of telling if they were living better?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No. No. I don't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 And most people had somebody doing their washing for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 For example the woman who did the washing - the charwoman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
There used to be two or three charwomen in Bradfield - used to go - you pay these - well they - they don't go out but they - they take in washing some of them now. Widows and things like that, one or two of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 The charwomen would be widows would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 That's right, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 So they'd be quite rest of than the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes, yes. Do it just for - try to earn a living.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Do you think that any groups in the village felt superior to other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Shopkeepers wouldn't feel themselves a bit above the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
I don't think there's anything like that. If one or two chaps go about now doing old peoples gardens and one thing and another but - a - a lot of 'em don't.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Were there any families in the village you thought were rough and some who were respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well not - not like it used to be. Not now, I mean to say, it used to be as you say, roughs and - but they're all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What sort of people would have been the rough families?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 People who go rabbiting and one thing and another when they shouldn't do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Would they be farm workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh well - and - even though they could they wouldn't be - don't go on other peoples farms to get rabbits.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 They wouldn't have a regular job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, no. Poachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What else did they do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Go on the river - catching fish and picking up }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7818127\charrsid16386455 w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 inkles and things like that. They could get a living somehow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 But they would have houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Live in a little cottage. If you could call 'em cottages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Can you remember a family like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes. No - no names.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 But you can actually remember people like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes, yes, yes. Yes, I shouldn't put names on in case I'm had up for defamation of character.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 So they'd be very poor people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Yes. No. Of course things are different now to what they were at that time. I mean to say, getting nine shillings a week farm labourers well now they're getting - I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 It's surprising how they could have lived on that isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Well - of course they used to have to go - do the same as dad did. Do little odd jobs. Shil - shilling here and a shilling there.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Your father sounds particularly skilled - he was obviously very good at that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
No - he's - taught himself of course. He wanted to earn a shilling and he - earned a shilling. Go and mend peoples clocks and - these striking clocks with the lines, you know, the weights on. Used to put new lines on and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was he better than most people at that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Well - be cheaper I expect to have somebody, you know, he was an amateur of course. Same as mending boots or anything. Done nearly all the village - boot repairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What do you think about his pigs - he kept pigs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. He'd keep pigs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What did he keep them on?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What did he keep 'em on? Well - meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was that quite expensive?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No - not at that time to what it is now. He'd get a sack of wheat for about five shillings - now - now it's about three pound I expect.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 And he'd sell one to make that up would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Oh yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How many did he have at a time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Ten as a rule. Sometimes he'd - he'd have been seven or eight perhaps - just buy the - the litter 
as he calls it. Go to the farms and buy them you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did your mother see herself as belonging to a particular group of people in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, she never belonged to - no, she never belonged to any - well there was no - there was no things like that at that time - no - no women
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7818127\charrsid16386455 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
s Institute or anything like that. Friendly with one or two people more than she was others perhaps but - she wasn't a - she wasn't a - one to have a lot of visitors in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 She wasn't a local girl was she like your father was fairly local?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, she was Ipswich - Woodbridge in fact - Woodbridge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did she feel sort of set apart from the villagers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh no. No, no, no, she was only - same - same as us. Poor - poor and glad to get anything she could 
get hold of. There's the - there's the gentleman that - bought that pub that I tell you that was pulled down - where the monument is. That was him as bought that and pulled it down and had that monument erected.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 He was a man from the Hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. 
Had - collected a pound from each family and he paid the rest. Just say that - it was - a village - village sight you see. Yes. His son was killed in the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 When you say they were gentlefolk, what were the characteristics of gentlefolk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well -
 people who - got money and didn't work for it. But he - he was a - something to do with the copper mines I think out in - in Africa. Yes, I think that's what he was. He - he - he supplied the government with copper or bron}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7818127\charrsid16386455 z}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 e or something like that I believe from his mines.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Good source of money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, yes. His son was killed in the war. He was the first - his son was the first to land an a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14632374\charrsid16386455 ir}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 plane on a ship. Yes, he was killed - he was killed after all. And a gentleman what used to live at South Lo
dge here, he - he had a son, he was killed in the war. Well they've both got stained - stained windows in the church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Who else in the village would you say didn't have to work for their money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well - there's investors I expect and - got it invested and they got the money I expect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was there anyone else who was in that position?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, I don't - no - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You thought the Canon was quite a busy man?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Canon - oh Canon Norman well of course he had the - he had the livings and three of his sons clergymen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 They worked quite hard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 One here and one at Brantham. I tell you they had to give up their farms because - of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You didn't feel they were gentlefolk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No. No, they were gentlefolk I expect but - they went t
oo far. There's one of my sisters - one of my sisters - well the one that's alive now - she was servant down there and - we used to go down there and get basins of dripping one thing and another. Well of course they - they had joints there of half a bullo
ck. Well they could get some lovely dripping. And - and she was cook - well in - in the kitchen anyway. We used to take a basin down there - enough dripping to last us for a month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was that allowed or was it sort of underhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 She had permission did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was she able to help you in any other way like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
No. Well some of the - some of the people used to send - send - things like that dripping or things like that down to the poor people you know.
 And of course we wasn't - we wasn't classes as poor people. Never was no. Well there was - we - down here at the - well myself from the time I was seven years old I - I expect I was seven 'til I - I left school I used to go down there every morning to ge
t milk. Used to go down - get their milk from the farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 So that was a way of earning a few pennies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
That's right. Yes. Then Christmastime of course we - we used to go down and have a party with the - with the servants and one thing and another. '
Cos they used to keep a dozen servants then, now they only keep one. In fact some of them don't do that now - they have to do it themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was there a servants hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh the servants hall, yes, yes, they had the - too storey like as - for the b
edrooms of course. Same as the Rectory here. Well the - the - Canon Normans sons what was here. Well all the previous ones when I went to school - well they got three storey - three storey and a basement. I mean, the - the Rectory was too - too big altoge
ther. Used to keep about eight servants. Besides the actual - outdoor servants. Chauffeur - or pony and carts then of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 They'd be extra on top of the eight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 There'd be the rector and his wife would there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Rector and his wife and about four - four - four kiddies. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 When you had these parties at Spa Lodge - what happened there who else would go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Games with the servants. Had - had a tea with the servants of course, then they'd see us home, the servants.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How much did you get for carrying their milk for them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
I couldn't tell you - about sixpence a week I expect - I couldn't tell you now. I think more - more or less mother used to get little things form there and we used to do it for nothing I believe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 That would be sort of things like dripping again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Yes. I mean to say, used to cart water for laundry people. Sister used to take it down to - to Jakes Hall - of a morning before she went to school. Take it back at night when it's ready or one night - not the same night of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Can you remember anyone that would be described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What - what my parents would say you mean. Well these people down here of course were - the same as Jakes Hall and - and the
 Rectory of course. They were all classes as - ladies and gentleman. They all - well - lot higher than what we were of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Do you remember seeing a policeman around here when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 There was always one stationed in the village. If we want -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was it this one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
No, no, no. This one's only six years old, this one we have now. Several - one, two, three - four, five, six, seven - nine - count seven since I've been out the Navy. Seven different houses had had police. They haven't
 been police houses you see - not - not 'til lately. First police house - for Bradfield's number ten council house down here. That was a council house but now they've got a police house. That's been built about six years and that's up for sale. It's only 
been built six years. Yes. Now evidently he's going down to Dovercourt you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 When you were a boy remember a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Had a policeman in every village then. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh well that all depends what - what 
- what you done. They used to carry a little stick all - or their gloves and give you a tap but now they mustn't do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What sort of thing would they give you a trap for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well anything wrong - if they see you doing anything wrong they'd vie you a belt but now you - they mustn't do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Can you remember that happening to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, many times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What sort of thing would you be doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh - things we shouldn't have been doing. Getting through fences or - pulling somebody else's
 fence about or something like that. Anything like that - what we shouldn't have been doing anyway. Still we - was always in the wrong so -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you ever feel he did it unjustly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, no. Not - we might have thought so at the time but - don't do i
t now of course. So they don't do half enough - well they're not allowed to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 When you were naughty did your mother ever say I'll call the policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did she mean it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 In fact they - well they - they told policem
en sometimes you know, yes, give a tip across the ear or something with a glove, that's all and - take no notice of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did your parents call the policeman in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, yes, yes, they're passing or anything like that well they'd go - done it for fun more than anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Sort of joke?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. To keep in with the policeman for one thing but still - that was - 'cos they had a policeman in every village then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was he generally looked on as somebody to be feared?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Oh yes, yes, yes. Penny was a penny at that time. In fact - a penny was as good as a pound now at that time. Yes. 'Course after we all left home well they had a quiet life. Deserved it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 At the time do you remember feeling anything about that - do you remember feeling resentful?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
No, because - mother - I mean to say, I - I was away from home - 'til she died. In fact I was in the Navy when she died so - she died in the September and I come out in - she - she died in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4657657\charrsid16386455 E}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 aster and I came out the Navy in September. She used to be proud of us when we come home in uniform. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 She didn't worry about you too much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was your father ever ill so he couldn't go to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Oh yes. Yes. Time he - once or twice. And after he - after he got off the railway he went to Bath for rheumatism. Yes. Well - Bath - some kind of water there didn't they - at Bath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did he have to pay for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 I don't know whether
 - whether a gentleman paid for him. He got him there but whether he paid for him I don't know - I don't think dad paid for it. But he paid for - paid for my mother's lodgings and that of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Who was the man who sent him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Gentleman down here - Mr Nichols. He - he's - he's dead.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was he a doctor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, no, just a friend of - of - he was - he's the son in law to that ganger that I was telling you about. He }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8134313 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455  the daughter. He was the only one that wasn't involved in the - in the fa
rm stunts. Mr Nichols - he was nice - they - after he died they moved to Bath and then she died but - the daughter comes and see me every year. She was here about four months ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 They were good friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Yes. Dad used to go down there and s
it with him - on the lawn and one thing another - in the summer time. He had a place built - a sun house built for - so they could sit in there. Nice gentleman he was.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What did he do for a living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Never done anything as I know - be what you'd c
all a gentleman at that time you see. Whether he had any investments or anything of course I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 When your father missed work for any reason did he get paid as normal or did he go without his pay if he didn't go to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, he had - he 
had his railway pension of course. His railway pension but - then he got the old age pension, of course he packed up work altogether then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 When he was working full time as normal and he missed work because he was ill - would he get paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh he'd - yes, he'd get paid - sick benevolence you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did your standard of living drop when he was ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
No. In fact I don't remember him being ill all the time I was - time was youngsters. I don't remember him being at home ill. He had the 'flu
 and one thing and another but - after - after we all left home. Same as they went to Bath - they were living by themselves then. Mum and dad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Were there any reasons that you had to go to the Guardians or the Parish or anyone like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Were there people in the village who did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 There used to be of course - on the parish. People on the parish used to get a loaf of bread a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Were they these same rough people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, yes. Now of course they - state - state keep 'em now don't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What else would they get besides bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Two and six a week - two and six and a loaf of bread I think it was they - they used to get. Once a week. What they call on - on - on the - on the village or something like that - I f
orget what they used to call it. But that's done away with of course since - unemployment and things like that come out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did the parish supply blankets or anything for mothers who were expecting babies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh - oh yes, yes. Yes, yes, yes, they done
 that, yes. So they do now I think. They serve out blankets and that if anybody needs 'em. Who run it I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Do you know of any other benefit like that that was available in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No - not that I know of. Well - come to think of it
 there didn't ought to be anything like that now. I mean to say - I mean to say - there don't ought to be any needy now. If they're not old age pensioners they - they get - benevolent - if there sick or anything don't they - or people that - there's every
thing provided for them now. At one time of course they used to lend you blankets and everything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You told me when you first came here you lived for a short time in a house up by the school - is that right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Just for a few months?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Could you tell me about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes - well I - I pointed that out to you you see because - the house is down now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 It's not there at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, not there at all. The - the porch is there, I told you. The house is there but the s
chool is not there. There was a porch - a porch was still the back ; the back entrance but the house was there you see. And that of course used to be the clothes - where we used to hang our clothes and that when we went in school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 So when you lived in that house you were practically on top of the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
No, no. No, we left that - the house and they turned it into a school and took the ceilings down to make - no, no, that wasn't - that wasn't occupied then - not - it was occupied as a house when 
we lived there but then they - turned it into the infants school - overflow do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How long were you in that house - how long did you live there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well - not long. Not long - about three or four months, then we shifted to here as I tell you.
 We shifted to this one. And we lived in that one - from - 18 - beginning of '83 'til - 1923.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 When you were very young did you have any lessons from your parents - school lessons at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, because going to school we wasn't allowed at home work. No. No, mother - mother wouldn't have that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You couldn't read before you went to school or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No. No. Not that I remember anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 She didn't have much time I suppose did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No. No. 'Course we went to school - about four and a half years old - five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you go full time when you first began?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Yes. Yes. Yes. Come home to dinner. There was no meals at school then you see. And one of us used to have to take the dinner down to - to the signal box to dad and we'd take ou
r own dinner then you see as well. Mother used to have the two dinners ready and - dad'd be looking out for us. As soon as he see us, out plates and dish it out and - have our dinner and shove off to school when - we never used to stop to bring the basket
 or can back or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was the school a church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 The chapel school was built later wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Not chapel school. No, no. The - the county school. The county school was built after - I don't know what time it was I'm 
sure. My youngest sister, she's seventy six, seventy-seven this year - in June - and she went to that school so - and where she - I expect she did go to this school for a time. But the old school - there was only one room you see, 'til they adde}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4657657\charrsid16386455 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455  this - th
is on for the infants school. No - no screens or anything - we were all in the one room and one teacher there for elder class perhaps and - used to be maps hanging round the school with pointers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you go to the infants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 I never no - I was in the other school when the infants school opened.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 So you didn't go to the infants school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, I - no, no, that wasn't - that wasn't there. That was turned into infants school afterwards. When we moved you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How many teachers would there be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 I don't remember - but - I was at the other school - I was young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 It was quite a long time ago?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Yes, but I mean to say, the - when - when - I only lived - we only lived in there three months - four months. So I must have - and I was on
ly thirteen months old when I come to Bradfield so I must have been in that house. But I never remember - going into the infants school in that school. Me sister what died she - she used to - she got up into ex seventh as we used to call it at that time a
nd then she went in there teaching - with the - the youngster. 'Course she - she was born in '87. I was born in '85 so she was six years - so I must have started in that school I should think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How long did she do that for - did she stay there some time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Well - 'til she went to service you know, she only - she's the only one - she's only one in that - in that class, ex seven they used to call it. She went right through and got to ex seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was that the highest standard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 That's the highes
t standard, see, well I - I went up - I got into the ex seventh. I went to Manning school to - to finish off. With a man - teacher you see, a male teacher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 But she stayed on as a pupil teacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well only just for - 'til she was old enough to go ser - leave home. About thirteen I suppose she may have -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 So she left that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Yes. She had her time in London and she come home to look after mother and dad. And then of course mother died and she stopped and looked after me and me dad. Dad lived - from - 1922 to 1950 after mother died you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was that your sister Ethel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, Mabel. Mabel. Her and myself was left single - kept single.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Ethel was the one who went to Australia?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. She lives there now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 At the school were there boys and girls together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 All together, yes, yes, all together. No male - no male teacher. First male teacher come with the new school of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How many teachers were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 There's a govern}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4657657\charrsid16386455 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 r, two teachers and a pupil teacher. What they call a pupil teacher. Miss Dale was the - the governess when I went to school. She }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8134313 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455  a miller at - from Dedham. The last time she died. Since I've been out the Navy the last time I heard of her she was in - a shipping booking office in Ipswich - in Commercial Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Do you know the name of the miller that she }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8134313 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 ?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, I think it was Webb if I remember right. Webb I think it was. I know it had - the - the miller was - dad used to get his pig meal off.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did the school children so much of the governors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 The govern - the governess or the - the governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you say governors or governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Governess. Woman - governess. Oh used to see her yes. Well used to come in every day and then of course we used - we used to have
 the examination every twelve month by - the inspector.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What would that be like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Just ordinary that's all. The whole lot of us used to - just sit down. She used to ask 'em questions. We might do a couple of sums then - arithmetic or something an
d - composition or something of that - writing and one thing and another. I know we always used to be very good. But if we were or not I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did he mark it there and then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes, yes, yes, yes. He'd ma}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4657657\charrsid16386455 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 k them and - and give you a lectur
e like at the end before he left saying you were very good, one thing and another. Always very good. But honestly - honestly speaking I - I can do - I can do things now which I - a sight better than they do now - the answers. You go into - go into Woollie
s or the Marks and Spencer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4657657\charrsid16386455 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 s - and then go to the next girl - and ask if that's correct.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Were you very frightened when the inspector came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No. No. I wasn't - I don't know about some of the others. I was always a good boy so I had - I never took a
ny notice who come in. 'Cos you never knew when they were coming you know. You didn't know whether there was going to be an examination or anything - they used to come in and there you are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Do you think the teachers were frightened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No. The teac
hers'd know who they were when - see they wasn't there, they'd call the register of course first. want to know where the others were well if the teachers didn't know they - - they didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 But the teachers weren't nervous of the inspectors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How long would it take you to get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How long? Well we used to live here and the school was in this road. 'Cos I said I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4657657\charrsid16386455 went to Manning}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 tree school last twelve months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How long did that take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well, used to have to go to - walk down to the station. Go to Mistley. Then walk from Mistley to Manning}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4657657\charrsid16386455 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 ree. But I didn't used to go along by the water as you say, I used to go long road you see. Then cut through.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 That would take quite a time wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. I - and we 
used to leave school - I used to come back by train. Used to get home here about quarter to five, I think the train used to come in quarter to five. Sometimes you used to have to walk from Manningtree because you missed the train messing about or somethin
g.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you get a cheap ticket?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Never got no ticket at all. Used to go down to Harwich, we never used to have tickets. Used to just - well they - people knew I was on - always used to say, see to my son - see from Bradfield. I used to go down to Harwich I tell you every-
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 That was free?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Used to go down to Harwich. They used to collect tickets - but they - they knew us all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 When you were at the school here did you en}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4657657\charrsid16386455 j}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 oy it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes. As - as things were I expect I did. I was always into - into trouble of some sort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You don't remember disliking it though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you like the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes, the teachers were very nice. They used to come and visit mother sometimes. To tell her - to tell her how good we were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 That was about you they'd come in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 All - any of us. They were friendly of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did they emphasi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4657657\charrsid16386455 z}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 e certain things as being very important, like manners or tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, not in them days. Thought there was anything wrong pe
rhaps they'd come and speak to mother - say, you know, so and so and so and so. Then we had a good lecture. We might be sent to bed with no tea or something of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What would that be fore?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well - something we'd done at school which we shouldn't have done I expect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Were they keen on punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Oh they were - used to call the register certain time - about five minutes after school opened. They'd call the register before the clergyman come for prayers anyway. We used to go into school
 at nine o'clock I think it was. Come out - twelve o'clock and back again at - half past one I think it was - I'm not positive.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What would happen to you if you were late for school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 I don't you ever were late. If we - if one - if one of us going
 to be late mother used to tell one of us to tell the teacher that so and so'd be a - a few minutes. He's just gone down to the station for dad or something of that - they'd know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 They wouldn't mind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No. We had no trouble with us at school - none at all. Boys - boys or girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Can you remember the other children being punished for anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes. Plenty of 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What would happen to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh used to - they used to have a cane and - teachers'd lay 'em across their knee or lay 'em across a chair and give 'em a c}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4657657\charrsid16386455 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 ning. It's no good their parents coming - to the school mistress about it either.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did the parents ever try that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 They used to come and complain sometimes but - the teacher'd turn round and say, if you come in here I'll give it to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Would the girls get caned as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Oh yes, rather.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Put across a chair and caned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Were your parents interested in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 The majority of it was a stick across the han
d. They wouldn't much laying across a desk or anything. You'd got to be very bad to - you put across the chair or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did your parents take an interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes, we always - well I say always - spare time - spare time we
'd have slates and one thing and another, pencils. Paper - paper, yes at school. But - mother wasn't - well, nor was dad - in favour of - of home lessons at all. But - if we - was playing school on our own they'd - they'd - see if they were right, one or 
the other, dad or mum. They were both very good scholars although dad was self taught.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Hadn't he been to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No. He went into harvest field nine years old. Dad did. He done his first - first harvest on Canvey Island when he was eleven years o
ld - using a scythe. Yes, yes. No machines you see, all done by hand. He worked with his uncle, his uncle used to sharpen his tools for him - Canvey Island, they lived on Canvey Island.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 So he couldn't read at all until he was older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, no, he taught himself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How did he do that - in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Down at the signal box and one thing and another, yes. No, no he never was - he taught himself to write and one thing and another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Quite late in life you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did your mother help him with that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, I don't think mother - I don't know whether mother - I remember whether mother went to school. Couldn't say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Do you think that was why they were so keen on you learning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 She'd tell you - if you give her half change anyhow. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Do you think this is why they were so keen on your school work - because they'd not had the chance themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 They - they used to help me if they could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you help them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well I expect we did. They used to do 
things different to what we did of course. They couldn't do sums much like we did. They could add up money perhaps. Sixpence and threepence make ninepence or something of that but - whatever it meant - I don't know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Would your mother ever go up to the school to see the teachers there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Only at - only - only - visiting days like or anything like that. Not - not - she wouldn't go up to school to make complaint or anything. No. It had to be something bad that was - was against us if she did go up to
 school. So I - been doing something or said something that - or anything like that. We come home and tell mother, perhaps she'd go up but - she wouldn't - in cases like that she - she wouldn't take our part, you know what I mean, just - she - se - see ju
stice done. She wouldn't take our part. If we was in the wrong we was in the wrong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did all the children come from similar types of home around the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 All farm labourers and all things like that of course - I expect people working on the ra
ilway was - far more - important than the people working on the land I suppose at that time. Yes. Got more money of course - paid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 That made a difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. But - dad - I said dad used to go all over the village doing different jobs. Special 
for old people. Putting their clocks right. Repairing boots. Doing - sharpening saws. Anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Do you think the feeling you got that your parents mixed with everyone was because your father was that kind of man rather than they were actually equal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
No, I think - they were all - well - all one class at that time. Dad might have got a shilling a week more than farmer labourers perhaps but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did the teachers single out }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9199196\charrsid16386455 some children for special treat}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 ment in school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, well - f
avourites you mean - no I don't think so. No, I don't think there was any favourites amongst 'em. They were all - all as one. Should be too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did the children have gangs and things at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Gangs? Oh I see what you mean - no, I don't think so. I daresay there was - some of them made chu}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9199196\charrsid16386455 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
s. Brothers and sisters, they'd have certain next door neighbours perhaps - I know we all used to play together, girls and boys you know. No. No favouritism I don't think. Youngsters come from the other end of th
e village to have a game they - they played. Used to go down on the shore one with the other and all mix up together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Were there any children who were left out at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well the - some of 'em - what you'd call 'em - different class I expect. Fath
ers - fathers and mothers always in trouble perhaps or something of that - poachers or something of that. Really that wasn't nothing to do with the youngsters of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 But would the children take it out on them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. It'd be taken out on the children you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What sort of things would you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Shun 'em altogether I expect - that sort of thing - not speak to 'em. Turn 'em adrift. But on - you get on - you get the whole lot along the shore well they all join up together - irrespective i
f there's any ill feeling at that time. At the school holidays I mean to say it - the shore used to be - packed. Well there used to be a lot of sand and that there no of course there's not. No sand and the river's pol}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9199196\charrsid16386455 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 uted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What sort of things would you get up to down there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Round and about - playing ball and cricket and cricket bats and one thing and another. Bats made out of a piece of wood - hopscotch and I don't know what you call it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 When you went on to the school in Manningtree were there many more teachers and more classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes, more classes and men teachers too you see. Schoolmasters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Were there different subjects there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Yes. Music as well - music lessons as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Far as I kne
w. You know, I - I never learned it up there so I didn't - I didn't improve much down there. I was in the choir too. But I mean to say our schoolmaster used to sit on a desk or a chair at the end of the school and used to do the notes you know - by himsel
f
 and used to - right down what what - what it was - doh, me, lah, fah and all like that. That'd always be the last lesson so if you didn't get it right you was late for - I used to be late sometimes. I never learned about music. But his son - he's a - a p
upil teacher, he used to come round checking us - I think he seen me a couple of good marks sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 That was the schoolmasters son?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Headmasters son. And I tell you the - three or four of the sisters started service at that ; at that master's school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 In his house you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 In his house, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 When you went there were there children from Manningtree mostly who went to that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What - oh yes, there was - there was - Manningtree youngsters, Mistley youngsters, Bradfiel
d youngsters. Well I think that's about two from Bradfield, I think that's all there was. Branthan, Caraway, they - they used to come to that - just to finish off you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 They were the brighter ones were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes - they got up as far as they could in the school and - then the - schoolmistress here has recommended to - Manningtree school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 So was it an honor to go there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, you used to - well - more advanced of course. Things - things that they didn't do up here. Certain lessons you d
idn't do up here. Music lessons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you feel yourself to be cleverer to go there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 I expect I did at the time but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How old were you when you left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 I - about thirteen. I started Mistley station at thirteen years old. I was in the offi
ce there - goods office. Four years I done on the railway. Before I joined the Navy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Would you have liked to have stayed at school longer if you had the chance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, I don't think so, hot at that time. I might do now perhaps if I was a youngster 
now I might but - I think I got up as far as I could. I - I went to I went to school again of course after I got in the Navy - to go through all different - mensuration and algebra - I've forgot all about it now. Had to go through that to pass the exam.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you go to evening classes when you were on the railway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No. No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Do you have any regrets about your education?
