\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 I wish I'd done more sometimes. 'Cos I - I done a lot of schooling while I was in the Navy but I forgot all about it now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Do you think you benefited from being at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Oh yes. Yes, yes. Well of course I should have got on the - I shouldn't have got on the railway if I hadn't have been - hadn't have been - well, advanced I - I expect you'
d call it - in schooling. Schoolmistress you see give you a character. And I went straight into the office and there you are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You thought yourself lucky to get that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 When you were at school you told me you were doing some odd jobs for neighbours like carrying water and that type of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Getting milk and - getting milk and one thing and another, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Who was that for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Lady named Mrs Barton, used to live in the big house - Mrs Barton, they moved to Bath after all. After I left home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did she pay you for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Well I couldn't say. I expect - about sixpence a week I expect. I couldn't tell you now - I really couldn't tell you how much it was. We used to go down there to parties and things like that you see. And used to go - go out and get the milk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How did you get the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well might be close I expect - neighbourly you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How often would you do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Every morning. Bar Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What would you do with the money you got for it - would you give it to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh we used to have money boxes, yes, put it in money boxes. Pay for shoes and things like that. Yes. Yes, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What did you do with the spare money you used to get for a job like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well we
 - used to go to Manningtree - we used to walk to Manningtree market for a ha'penny. And - to get - a penny for a - three hours job well a - youngster was as good as his father getting ten shillings a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was there anything else you did besides getting milk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Carting water as I said for the laundry. Well any odd job we used to do for different people. More than they w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9199196\charrsid16386455 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 ll do today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How old were you when you started doing these things?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well I used to go down to Harwich - shopping Saturday morning at eight - eight years old. And that was before that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You started before eight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Oh yes. Well nearly as soon as we could walk I expect we had to do jobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 When you left school you went to work on the railways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Railway. At Mistley - I started at Mistley, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How did you get that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well I don't - dad was on the railway, I expect he - the station master as Mistley. Got me a job I expect. Started in the office.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What exactly did you do in that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well I done clerk I was for in that office you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What was the name of the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Well we - we - goods clerk we was called on - on the payroll - goods clerk. Junior I'd be you see. then I went to - Harwich. Oh me own there - both goods and - the passenger. That was more - that was a small station you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What did the passenger work involve?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Telling the trains, issuing the tickets and things like that you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 And then you went on to another station?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 From Harwich I went to - Frmlingham - in the goods office there. Under clerk again - two of us there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You'd gone back to the same kind of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, yes. And from there to - Norton, next to Woodbridge. The same again. I was - and passenger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How long were you in each of those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well probably - eleven months to twelve months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 In each one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 In each one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What hours would you work as a goods clerk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well that all depends what time the station opened - it was eight o'clock. Eight o'clock 'til
 five o'clock. Eight o'clock to five o'clock. Of course if you - in - in the passenger office - ticket office we used - working a bit later you see - stay for the last train.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you ever have to work Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. We - we used to take it in turn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7683218\charrsid16386455 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 . Had two clerks you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 So it would be every other Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. We had a good clerk would take the - the passenger clerk, you see, passenger tickets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 So it was sort of half staff Sunday?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you always work on Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. And Sundays, yes. Half day Saturdays. Half day, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you have holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Four days we used to get.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 The same as your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Same as father, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Can you remember what you - got as a goods clerk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Well the most I got was ten shillings a week but I couldn't tell you exactly what I got at each station. I expect at Mistley I was getting about five shillings I expect - I couldn't really say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 When you first began you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you feel the money was fair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 At that time, yes. That wouldn't do now though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you give any of the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh she had the lot. About six - when I - at Mistley - of course when I was away they used to - they used to hav
e to supply me with a little money. I didn't get enough to pay for lodgings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 So in fact you were making a loss?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did that seem very unjust to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well - I say we didn't take any notice of it at that - in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How did you get on with the people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Oh very well. Though of course I - I - at Mistley I was at - with three more - three more clerks. At the - the other stations I was on me own you see. And I was on me own at - Ca}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4917765\charrsid16386455 rod}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455  - passenger and goods. Atm - framlingham I was in goods office and at Norton I was there again passenger and - just the one chap on the station besides the station master you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 But at Mistley you were quite friendly with the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes, yes, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Were they boys as well like yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh no, no, they - no. One of 'em'd be - well - just on - the head clerk would be just on training for station master.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How did the station master treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well all right. Yes. He wa
s nice enough man he was. Mr Parker at Mistley. Used to give me half a dozen eggs sometimes. I used to go around collecting eggs for him if he asked us.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 He'd be a neighbour almost?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Lived near the station you see. Then eventually went out to Clacton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you have the same good relations with the other station masters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes, yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Where did you live when you got the job where you had to live away from home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Lodgings - in lodgings - in lodgings, yes. That's what I say, mother used to have to send me some money to pay for me lodgings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4917765\charrsid16386455 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
 a farm house you lived in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
No - well - well at - at - Carod when I went to Carod I lodged with the signalman. He had - he had three jockey lodgers as well. Yes, he was close to Newmarket - at Newmarket you see and he had three jockeys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You were all full time lodgers were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Yes, yes. Played cards at the night and one thing and another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Then when you left the railway you joined the Navy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 I joined the Navy. Joined the Navy at Harwich.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What made you do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 'Cos I thought I'd change. Get out of the other - there wasn't enough money and I went as assistant - you got everything found you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What did you start as when you joined the Navy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Boy - boy second class. Boy second class when you go into training then first class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you know someone who was in the Navy or what put the idea into your head?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well living close to Harwich.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Common thing was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Oh yes. There was a lot of boys from here went to - in the Navy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 When you started what hours did you work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What - in the Navy? Well you - can't - you're on duty twenty-four hours a day. In the Navy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you get any time off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well you - you - you'd get your time off of course - four hours on, four hours off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 And it would be the Royal Navy you joined?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes. The Royal - yes, not the merchant navy. Royal - Royal Navy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Had you joined because of the war - did you join to go to war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Oh I joined up during the South African war - 'til that time. I was just finishing me training though when that - when the - when I was on the - about - the South African war - the Boer war. Time the ships were out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How old were you then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Sixteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 So you went to South Africa with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 I didn't go out to - to South Africa, just backwards and forwards on the - half way perhaps you see, 'cos we was under sail then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You'd take people to a certain point and another ship would pick them up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, just escort that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You were a boy second class all this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, same as I - what I was saying - last year I finished me training on that ship then I was first class boy. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What were your duties as a second class boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Well - do all training - training all the time you see. We - we was training all the time. The instructors you see, we had instructors you see. There used to be some kids too some of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How old were you when you were a boy first class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Eighteen. That's when you start your Navy - that's when you start your pension - eighteen. Boys service don't count for - for pension you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What rank had you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Boy first class then. Then ordinary seaman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How old were you when you became an Ordinary Seaman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Eighteen. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You were a boy second class when you were sixteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Sixteen to seventeen. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Then you were first class seventeen to eighteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 So when you were an Ordinary Seaman what were your duties then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
All depends what they put you to do. It might be - messman for P.O's or Warrant Officers or things like that. And of course there's the other training just the same - while you was Ordinary Seaman you
 see, under training. Yes, we'd be - under instructions - morning and - and afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You were telling me about them making you go up aloft?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes, that was in - that was - when we was boys that was. 'Course they done away with sailing ships s
oon after that. Well - the change - the change over would be about - 1901. 1901 because they done away with the old square rigged ships one and the other and the boys used to go into barracks then you see. They done their training on land then - as they d
o now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How long were you an ordinary seaman for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
I don't know - about nine months. Then passed for Able Seaman. Then Able Seaman to Leading Seaman. Leading Seaman to second class Petty Officer. They - they done away with that - first - first class Petty Officer. Then Chief you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You were an instructor yourself at one time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes I was instructor, yes. I went out to Australia - instructor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 When was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 During the first world war. 1917 - February 1917 I went out to Australi
a. And I come home 1920 - December. December 1920. Then I finished me time at Chatham barracks. Naval barracks. That's - that's done away with now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 That was two more years was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Twenty-two years you see I done for pension.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 When you were first in the Navy you got more money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 When I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How much did you get when you first became a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Sixpence a week. Sixpence a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What did you get as an Ordinary Seaman - can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 One and a penny a day I think it was. I
 couldn't - couldn't remember that. I know they get - they get more in a day now than what I got in a month. That was after doing twenty-two years service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Would you send the money you got home to your mother or could you not afford to do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Well as you advanced a little bit - we did - we could do send it to your mother if you liked but I used to send mine to a - a bank in Chatahm dockyard you see. Save it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was that quite a common thing to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes, yes. Right up to the time as I come out the Navy. I - I had that house built from money I got in - there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You were saying that during the first world war when conscription came in the people who were conscripted got more money than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, yes. They - the conscripts got more money than what - what I got as instructor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was there some trouble about that at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Yes, well so there was in the Army and Navy you see, so I mean that increased - they were only getting a shilling a day, the Army. Well the Navy wasn't much better.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How much did the conscripts get?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Five and something a day I think - I couldn't really say - couldn't really say-
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you get your money increased later?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, no, no, no, only as your rank - well they - they increas
ed - they increased Navy and - an Army during the war otherwise there'd have been a mutiny you see. That - that wasn't much I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 So you would call it unequal pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How did you feel about the discipline of the Navy - did you mind it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
Oh terrible it was then. 'Cos it's getting better of course all the time. The instructors used to knock the boys about and everything else at that time. They soon put a stop to that after - after a time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did they have floggings and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Oh yes. I don't know what to think - I don't know what year it was they done away with the cane and the birch.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What sort of things would you do to get that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well - simple things you know - boys used to get the cane if they - they wer
e caught smoking or had a cigarette on 'em or anything they used to get the cane. Six strokes or something like that. All depends what - what the crime was. It was a crime then of course - smoking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Were you allowed to smoke when you got older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 When you - eighteen, yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you feel that it was very unjust or did you feel you had to have that discipline?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well - at that time was just I expect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You felt that was all right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes - oh yes. I never had any of it. I was a good boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you ever feel like chucking it in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 When you started life in the Navy you had lessons then didn't you - you went back to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes, yes, yes. Yes, yes, went to school then of course you was under the instru
ctor all the time. That's in working hours. From nine o'clock 'til twelve. And two 'clock 'til four - you was under instructor. Then of course sometimes you used to have to do night times, things like that. Night - night instruction.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was this practical instruction?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes. Seamanship of course - seamanship. And school - used to go to school of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did it make you feel you wished you'd done some more work at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How much leave did you get?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 We used to get -
 four days at Easter. Fourteen days at Christmastime I think it was - or - if you was going on commission or anything like that. used to get your commission leave, fourteen days. Then when you come back of course - you done three years you come back and g
ot six weeks - six weeks leave you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What countries did you go to in your travels?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well - well according - Portugal, Greece, Italy, Turke}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4917765\charrsid16386455 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 . Crete - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4917765\charrsid16386455 through}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
 the Dardenelles through the Striats of Messina, up the Adriatic. I done three commissions up in - in - Malta - stationed at Malta. Then of course I done three years as I said in Australia. During the first world war.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Australia was the only place you went to during the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 That's all - yes. Well - the first - first pa
rt of the - the first - the first world war, the first part of it in Massadonia, I was in - battle of - Fallen Olives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 When you went to all these places you mentioned did you get time of to go ashore?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes. Yes, yes, oh yes. Get leave. Afterno
on leave - all depends what day it was of course. One day during the week and Sunday. That's providing - you was in a country where you could go ashore.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What sort of things would you do when you went ashore?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Walk around. Walk around - have a loo
k round. Went to Naples - in the glass works - see 'em blowing glass and - brought some things home I expect - gone now. Birches and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you send presents back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, yes. I've got lot of - lots of - lots of pieces of china from different - places. Barcelona and S}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4917765\charrsid16386455 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 lonica and S}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4917765\charrsid16386455 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4917765\charrsid16386455 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 nica I think they call it now - Turkey, Constantinople - Istanbul now isn't it. Constantinople when I was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 When you left home and went into the Navy did it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4917765\charrsid16386455 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 hange your relationship with your brothers and sisters at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No. It eased them a bit I expect - one - one less mouth to feed. That what you meant? Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you write to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes. Regular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 All of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, only home. No, couldn't afford penny stamps - not a lot of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You wrote to your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes. Yes. Kept in touch with them. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 How often would you write?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Every week. Because the others used to write birthdays just - things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Would they write to you every week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What happened on Sunday when you were in the Navy - was that kept as a day of rest or did work carry on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, used - well, used to scrub decks and everything first thing in the morning. About nine o'clock time used 
to start Sunday and go to church at ten. Had church on board you see of a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Who would take that - would it be the Captain?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Captain if - it was Captain if there was no Chaplain on board. It all depends the size of the ship you see. If it wa
s a battle ship you carried your own - parsons. Oh yes. And - the fleet would carry a Roman Catholic Priest as well. One for the fleet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 And he would sort of be moved around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Were there any provisions for chapel people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Ther
e was - there was - if you was in Malta or anything like that where there was an English chapel we used to go - used to have to go to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You got permission to go to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, well compul - compulsory.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did everyone have to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 All them
 that was off duty. Roman - Roman Catholic if there was no - if there was no Petty Officer or anything - a Roman Catholic well - one of others'd have to take 'em to the church and stop outside. He might go - he could go inside I expect, I don't know. I ne
ver went inside anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What would have happened if you'd not had a religion - would you have had to have gone to a church of some kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well - I don't know about that. They used to hold a - if there was no - if there was no Roman Catholic - well
, if we was in a foreign country with the same, you know, you'd have a - Roman Catholics would go one part of the ship for their service and take one - one of the Petty Officers would take it or something of that. If there was no officer on - Roman Cathol
ic. I used to take the Roman Catholics ashore Sunday after Sunday at Malta.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 When you had spare time on the ship how did you spend it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Mending clothes and doing things like that. Sing songs of a night time, dancing you know what I mean. We carried a band and nice dance.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you play anything in the band?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No. No. No, no. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 If they played - if they got a band used to play band.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 So there was a special one put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, yes, oh yes. Any ship with a complement over a certain amount could have a band you see. Bandmaster and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you read books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 I didn't but you could do if liked to. I wasn't fond of reading myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Was there any chance to meet girls at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh well I - I never went out with girls. No. Th
ey - they used to go ashore of course. There used to be dance halls and different places of course. When the crew went ashore.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you ever bring the friends you made on board ship home to meet your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No. No. I never did. But - me brother used to bring friends home sometimes but he - stopped there you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you ever go and spend your leave with other friends at other friends homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes, yes, I used to go to different - some people, Ipswich and one thing and another when I 
was on holiday. I used to go to Ipswich and pick them up and I'd go to their place and they'd come over here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 They were friends you'd made before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, in the ship, yes. Other people that was on the ship with you perhaps you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you tend to be on ships with people who came from where you came from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
When you were working on the railway and you finished work for the day, what sort of things would you do then before you went into the Navy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well I used to go to 
the lodgings and sit there reading or something like that you know. Play draughts or something of that - dominoes or something of that. I never went out much not when I was in lodgings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You'd play draughts with the jockeys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What else did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
What - irrespective of I - to pass the time away? Play different cards and things like that. Dominoes, draughts, all depends what you can play, chess. But the - the - the jockeys never went out much you know. They'd be - they'd be tir
ed by the time they'd finished their days work. Used to sit and play cards - 'til bed time at night of course. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you get a chance to make any other friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well that all depended if you was a friendly nature. I never did, no. No. Never had a girl in me life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 When you lived at home before you went into lodgings did you make new friends then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 After - after I joined the Navy do you mean? Oh before I left home, no, school pals and that was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No new friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What sort of things would you do with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well what games were on - they had seasons for marbles and seasons for - I don't know what you call it, hopscotch-
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 After you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes, yes,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did your parents like to know where you were when you were out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Did you have to be in by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 
When you was in lodgings you mean? At home? Well - if mother - mother thought it was time for us to go to bed she'd sing out to us and we'd have to go}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4917765\charrsid16386455  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 that's - we had no - no particular time, no. School - school - when we was at school we used to go to bed earlier than we did when the holidays were on of course. Sometimes they were looking for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 But when you'd finished school and were working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 You'd still have to go when your mother told you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 No, I mean we wasn't - we was looking for - age I expect.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 In some places when there were people in the village who did something which the other people didn't like they used to go
 to their houses and make what was called rough music outside the house, hanging saucepans, this kind of thing, did you know anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh - I - I don't know - unless that was - unless that was a - a party was very much disliked, they'd drum
 her out of the village. Might be that or-
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Do you remember that happening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Oh yes, oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4600328 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 What sort of thing would she have done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6909549 AB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6883735\charrsid16386455 Well - unsociable I expect. Been unsociable. Interfering with other peoples business and things li
ke that. They was glass to get rid of her out of the street. They'd - bang tins and one thing and another. She used to - when - when they were gone away.
